@iacore It can be explored (feel free to create a plugin if you want to play with it), but I was more inclinated to blocking access. Poisoning the content always felt as a little hacky to me. It doesn't fix the problem (indiscriminate requests to the server from AI bots) but only add more noise to the environment.

I know that detecting AI bots is hard or even imposible, since bots are more sofisticated and probably they eventually will use real browsers to don't be detected. Maybe something like Anubis can work.

