The following data loader should pull data from a spreadsheet and return an array of sheet objects:

```js
import { readFile, utils } from 'https://deno.land/x/sheetjs/xlsx.mjs';

function wbLoader(path) {
  const wb = readFile(path);
  return wb.SheetNames.map(n => ({
    name: n,
    data: utils.sheet_to_json(wb.Sheets[n])
  }));
}

site.loadData([".xlsx"], wbLoader);
```

When testing, the array is translated into an object without the `length` field.

For example, with the test file [users.xlsx](https://github.com/lumeland/lume/files/9396848/users.xlsx), the loader function generates the Array:

```js
[
  {
    name: "USA",
    data: [
      { name: "Oscar Otero", color: "black" },
      { name: "Laura Rubio", color: "blue" }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: "Europe",
    data: [
      { name: "Ozzy Osbourne", color: "black" },
