I just fixed it. You can try the dev version (`lume upgrade --dev`) as long as the new version is not published.

Additionally, a way to fix it in the stable Lume version is returning the data in the `content` property. Example:

```js
function wbLoader(path) {
  const wb = readFile(path);
  return {
    content: wb.SheetNames.map(n => ({
      name: n,
      data: utils.sheet_to_json(wb.Sheets[n])
    }))
  };
}
```

