Comments.Body:
The same file cannot be copied and rendered. A way to achieve that is generating a page with the markdown code for each post. For example:

```js
// ./markdown.tmpl.js

export default function * ({ search }) {
  for (const page of search.pages("type=post")) {
    yield {
      url: page.data.url + "source.md",
      content: page.data.content
    }
  }
}
```

This file generate a new page for each post, adding `source.md` at the end of the url. For example, the url `/posts/first-post/` will have the `/posts/first-post/source.md` page.

`search` is a global function available in the data object.

```tsx
export default function ({ search }) {
  const pages = search.pages("type=post", "date=desc", 5);
  return <ul>
    {pages.map((page) => <li><a href={page.url}>{page.title}</a></li>}
  </ul>
}

