If you want to reuse this data in other pages, you may want to import them from a `_data` file:

```js
// ./_data/api.js

// Fetch your data from anywhere
const response = await fetch("https://my-api.com/data.json");
const data = await response.json();

// Export it with the desired format
export default data;
```

Now you can access to this data from any page in the same (sub)folder:

```njk
<ul>
{% for item in api %}
    <li>{{ item.id }}</li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
```

More info about shared data: https://lume.land/docs/creating-pages/shared-data/#the-_data-directories

